<a name="0">[0]</a> <a href="#0" id=0>If designers and programmers think about the apparent mental qualities that their programs will have, they'll create programs that are easier and pleasanter -- more humane -- to deal with.</a>
<a name="1">[1]</a> <a href="#1" id=1>However, we must be careful not to ascribe properties to a machine that the particular machine doesn't have.</a>
<a name="2">[2]</a> <a href="#2" id=2>While we will probably be able, in the future, to make machines with mental qualities more like our own, we'll probably never want to deal with machines that are too much like us.</a>
<a name="3">[3]</a> <a href="#3" id=3>They should rather think of their program as a servant, whose master, the user, should be able to control it.</a>
